  "prompt": "I have my exams coming up. Personal issues are bothering me a lot. I don't want to mess up my studies this time. I'm not able to concentrate. I'm stressed emotionally and mentally. What should I do?",
  "response": "Here are some helpful strategies to manage stress and improve concentration:\n\n1. Mental Health Management\n- Practice deep breathing exercises\n- Meditate for 10-15 minutes daily\n- Talk to a counselor or trusted friend\n- Consider short-term professional counseling\n\n2. Study Techniques\n- Create a structured study schedule\n- Break study sessions into smaller, manageable chunks\n- Use the Pomodoro technique (25 min study, 5 min break)\n- Study in a quiet, distraction-free environment\n\n3. Self-Care\n- Get adequate sleep (7-8 hours)\n- Eat nutritious, balanced meals\n- Exercise regularly\n- Stay hydrated\n- Limit screen time before studying\n\n4. Stress Reduction\n- Practice positive self-talk\n- Avoid negative thinking\n- Accept that some things are beyond your control\n- Listen to calming music\n- Try journaling to process emotions\n\n5. Study Support\n- Form study groups\n- Use active learning techniques\n- Take practice tests\n- Review notes consistently\n- Seek help from teachers/professors if needed\n\nRemember, your mental health is priority. Be kind to yourself and take one step at a time. You can manage this challenging period.\n\nWould you like to discuss any specific concerns or strategies in more detail?",
